        "text": "The Russian mafia was also involved and, according to [[Alfredo Schulte-Bockholt]], who has studied the interaction or amalgamation of political and criminal structures in Russia before and after the end of the Soviet Union, had a not inconsiderable influence on the fact that the rule of law, despite its anchoring in the 1993 constitution, was difficult to implement in legal practice in the early years. According to him, the infiltration of the power structures within the former Soviet states by the mafia not only delayed economic reforms, but also led to the fact that legal companies were downright forced to cooperate with the mafia. The weakness of the state became increasingly apparent."
